HNO_INFO.name: HNO_INFO
HNO_INFO.description: This table contains common information from General Use Notes items. This table focuses on time-insensitive, once-per-record data while other HNO tables (e.g., NOTES_ACCT, CODING_CLA_NOTES) contain the data for different note types.

columns.name: NOTE_ID
columns.description: The unique ID of the note record.

columns.name: NOTE_TYPE_NOADD_C_NAME
columns.description: This virtual item is populated with a category value from Note - Type No-Add (I HNO 51) according to the following logic: * if Note - Type No-Add (I HNO 51) is populated, use the value directly * if Note - Type No-Add (I HNO 51) is null and the note is not ambulatory, return null * if Note - Type No-Add (I HNO 51) is null and the note has an ambulatory encounter context, obtain a category from the UCN note type (I HNO 34033) and map that value to an equivalent category from Note - Type No Add (I HNO 51), if possible
entries: Home Health Face to Face Attestation
Home Health Plan of Care Header

columns.name: PAT_ENC_CSN_ID
columns.description: The unique contact serial number for the patient encounter to which the note is attached. This number is unique across all patient encounters in your system. If you use IntraConnect this is the Unique Contact Identifier (UCI).

columns.name: ENTRY_USER_ID
columns.description: The unique ID of the user who created this note. This column is frequently used to link to the CLARITY_EMP table.

columns.name: ENTRY_USER_ID_NAME
columns.description: The name of the user record. This name may be hidden.

columns.name: IP_NOTE_TYPE_C_NAME
columns.description: The note type associated with this note.
entries: Home Health Plan of Care Certification Statement

columns.name: TX_IB_FOLDER_C_NAME
columns.description: Stores the Type of Message (I EOW 30) In Basket folder to be used by the Transcription interface to generate In Basket messages
entries: Merge Notification for Patients with Histories Contacts
Unmerge Notification for Patients with Histories Contacts
Proxy Access Level Transition Locked Records Message
Event Mon - New Managed Access Patient

columns.name: CREATE_INSTANT_DTTM
columns.description: The note's create instant.

columns.name: DATE_OF_SERVIC_DTTM
columns.description: The note's date of service.

columns.name: LST_FILED_INST_DTTM
columns.description: The instant the note was last edited.

columns.name: UPDATE_DATE
columns.description: The date and time when this row was created or last updated in Clarity.

columns.name: CURRENT_AUTHOR_ID
columns.description: This item stores the current author of the note for indexing purposes.

columns.name: CURRENT_AUTHOR_ID_NAME
columns.description: The name of the user record. This name may be hidden.

columns.name: VISIT_NUM
columns.description: Professional billing visit number attached to this note.

columns.name: CRT_INST_LOCAL_DTTM
columns.description: This is a virtual item that gets the create instant (I HNO 17105), in local time format.

columns.name: NOTE_PURPOSE_C_NAME
columns.description: This is a virtual item that displays the note purpose. It was previously stored in Note - Purpose (INP-5045).

columns.name: PRIORITY_YN
columns.description: The priority of the note (Yes = High, No = Routine).

columns.name: CONVERSATION_MSG_ID
columns.description: The record for the message that was also filed as a note. The text filed in the message and the quicknote will be the same and displaying one of these to the end user should be sufficient.

columns.name: HNO_RECORD_TYPE_C_NAME
columns.description: Record type.

columns.name: ACTIVE_C_NAME
columns.description: Whether the note is active. This item is not populated for all notes.

merged.name: HNO_INFO_2
merged.description: This table contains common information from General Use Notes items. This table focuses on one time only data while other HNO tables (e.g., NOTES_ACCT, CODING_CLA_NOTES) contain the data for different note types.
